#: of numpy.linalg.lstsq:24
msgid ""
"Cut-off ratio for small singular values of `a`. For the purposes of rank "
"determination, singular values are treated as zero if they are smaller than "
"`rcond` times the largest singular value of `a`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/linalg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.linalg.lstsq:29
msgid ""
"If not set, a FutureWarning is given. The previous default of ``-1`` will "
"use the machine precision as `rcond` parameter, the new default will use the "
"machine precision times `max(M, N)`. To silence the warning and use the new "
"default, use ``rcond=None``, to keep using the old behavior, use "
"``rcond=-1``."
msgstr ""

